verbs.description: outfeel (third-person singular simple present outfeels, present participle outfeeling, simple past and past participle outfelt)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To feel more accurately or more acutely than.
examples: Machines can outfeel a Helen Keller, out-taste and out-smell the best wine and perfume testers; they can discern pitch more unerringly than Stokowsky, and finer color hues than Rafael.
